examples.code:
```
// Basic numeric greater than or equal to check.
var x = 5;
var y = 4;
console.log(x >= 5);
console.log(x >= 6);
console.log(x >= y);
```

```
// Basic string greater than or equal to check. Case matters for string comparison.
var x = "apples";
var y = "Apples";
console.log(x >= "apples");
console.log(x >= "bananas");
console.log(x >= y);
```
